snippet.textDisplay:
I mean no disrespect to the artist, she seems super talented and I wish her well, however, I was expecting a traditional Punjabi folk artist being represented in this video. The modern Lahori elite does not represent Punjab or its culture, not even an inch. A small bunch who have ditched their own language and culture do not represent their people. Maybe the intention of this song was not to showcase Punjab but to highlight Pakistan's urban artists, but regardless of that it is not fair to represent all other provinces and to exclude the largest ethnic group in the country. 

On another note, this is a great initiative by Coke studio and Ali Hamza. Absolutely loving it. Coke studio is definitely in safe hands with him in the creative seat :)
